17/05/2010
LA PAZ, Bolivia -- Three Serbs were among six victims killed in a suspected drug trafficking incident in the province of Santa Cruz, police announced on Saturday (May 15th).
The other three victims were Bolivians;
a fourth was badly wounded.
A shoot-out between drug smuggling gangs erupted late Friday.
According to media reports, the Serbs had been working as bodyguards for Bolivian William Rosales Suarez, who was kidnapped by gunmen Friday.
Local police describe him as "the ringleader of a drug-trafficking gang in Santa Cruz".
(RTS, Tanjug - 16/05/10;
Latin American Herald Tribune, Reuters, AP - 15/05/10)
